name: CDC Retrospective Forecasts
description: Guidelines and forecasts for a collaborative U.S. influenza forecasting project.

targets.name: Season onset
targets.description: Conditional on onset occurring, the probability distribution across weeks within the influenza season for which week will be the first week above the regional threshold. The date should be specified as the *Monday* of the epidemic week that is the predicted first week above the threshold.

targets.name: Season peak week
targets.description: The peak week is defined by the Monday of the MMWR surveillance week in which the weighted ILINet percentage is the highest for the given season in a given region.

targets.name: Season peak percentage
targets.description: The peak percentage is defined as the highest numeric value that the weighted ILINet percentage reaches during the given influenza season in a given region.

targets.name: 1 wk ahead
targets.description: One- to four-week ahead forecasts will be defined as the weighted ILINet percentage for the target week.

targets.name: 2 wk ahead
targets.description: One- to four-week ahead forecasts will be defined as the weighted ILINet percentage for the target week.

targets.name: 3 wk ahead
targets.description: One- to four-week ahead forecasts will be defined as the weighted ILINet percentage for the target week.

targets.name: 4 wk ahead
targets.description: One- to four-week ahead forecasts will be defined as the weighted ILINet percentage for the target week.
